{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "APPS (Hendrycks et al, 2021a) serves as a benchmark for code generation, specifically evaluating the ability to generate Python code.",
    "Other datasets such as DS-1000 (Lai et al, 2023), HumanEval (Chen et al, 2021), MTPB (Nijkamp et al, 2023), and ODEX (Wang et al, 2023h) investigate code generation abilities in different forms.",
    "DS-1000 introduces data science problems related to seven Python libraries.",
    "HumanEval assesses LLMs using manually written programming problems, mitigating data leakage concerns to some extent.",
    "MTPB tasks LLMs with synthesizing a subroutine at each step, requiring consideration of both the current task description and previous steps."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "APPS (Hendrycks et al, 2021a) serves as a benchmark for code generation, specifically evaluating the ability to generate Python code.",
